There are {{{b}}}33 statements{{{/b}}} in this survey.{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}They are presented one by one at the top of the screen in the gray box. Tap on the appropriate button to assign a value to each statement according to your perspective. {{{br /}}}{{{br /}}} If you feel that the statement is {{{b}}}similar to your perspective{{{/b}}}, tap the green "+" button.
        {{{br/}}}{{{br/}}} {{{center}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/evalBoxes.svg?raw=true"  width="200"/}}}{{{/center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}If you feel that the statement is {{{b}}}different from your perspective{{{/b}}}, tap the red "-" button. {{{br /}}}{{{br /}}} If you are uncertain about a statement, tap the "?" in the white box. {{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}If you later want to {{{b}}}change{{{/b}}} your evaluation, tap the {{{b}}}redo icon{{{/b}}} next to the statement.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}} {{{center}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/redoBox.svg?raw=true" /  width="200" /}}}{{{/center}}}{{{br/}}}{{{br /}}}You can adjust the size of the text and view area by using the buttons at the bottom of the page.
        {{{br/}}}{{{center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/adjText.svg?raw=true"  width="150"/}}}{{{/center}}}
        {{{br/}}}{{{br/}}} {{{center}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/adjView.svg?raw=true"  width="150"/}}}{{{/center}}}{{{br /}}}If you want to see these instructions again, tap the "?" button at the top of the main page.{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}{{{center}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/helpSymbol.png?raw=true" width="30"/}}}

During this stage you will be asked to refine the evaluations you made in the previous step. {{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}Please {{{b}}}review the statements{{{/b}}} carefully. {{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}First, you will be asked to select those that are {{{b}}}most similar{{{/b}}} to your perspective. {{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}Then, you will be asked to select those that {{{b}}}differ the most{{{/b}}} from your perspective.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}To {{{b}}}select a statement{{{/b}}}, tap on the statement container. The color of the statement will change to yellow.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}When you have selected the {{{b}}}correct number{{{/b}}} of statements, the color of the {{{b}}}"Submit"{{{/b}}} button will change to {{{b}}}blue{{{/b}}}. Click on the Submit button to move to the next step.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}You may need to {{{b}}}scroll down{{{/b}}} to view all of the statements before you tap the Submit button.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}To make it easier to compare the statements, you can {{{b}}}reorder{{{/b}}} them by tapping on the up and down arrows located on the right or left sides of the statement.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}{{{center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/upDownArrows.svg?raw=true"  width="250"/}}}{{{/center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}
        You can also {{{b}}}move a group of selected statements{{{/b}}} to the top of the list by {{{b}}}long pressing{{{/b}}} (about 1 second) on the arrows to the {{{b}}}right side{{{/b}}} of the statements.{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}{{{center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/longPressArrow.svg?raw=true"  width="250"/}}}{{{/center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}
        If you want to see these instructions again, tap the "?" button at the top of the main page.{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}{{{center}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/helpSymbol.png?raw=true" width="30"/}}}

The statements have been ranked based on your previous evaluations.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}} Those statements that are closest to your perspective should be at the top of the view area in the darker green colored sections.{{{br /}}}{{{center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/GroupColors.png?raw=true"  width="150"/}}}{{{/center}}}{{{br /}}}Those that are farthest from your perspective should be at the bottom of the list in the darker red colored sections.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}You will need to {{{b}}}scroll down{{{/b}}} to see all of the statements.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}Please {{{b}}}review the rankings{{{/b}}} and make any necessary changes to the ranking of the statements so that the ordering {{{b}}}accurately reflects your perspective{{{/b}}}. {{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}{{{mark}}}This is the most critical stage of the survey, so please review the statement rankings carefully and change the positions of the statements if necessary.{{{/mark}}}{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}  
        To {{{b}}}swap the positions of neighboring statements{{{/b}}}, tap the up or down arrows on the right or left side of the statement.{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}{{{center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/sortUpDownArrows.svg?raw=true"  width="250"/}}}{{{/center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}To {{{b}}}swap the positions of statements that are separated{{{/b}}}, tap the statement boxes to select the two statements (the statement color will change to yellow) and a swap confirmation message will automatically appear.{{{br/}}}

        {{{br /}}}{{{center}}}{{{br /}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/sortSwap.svg?raw=true"  width="250"/}}}{{{/center}}}{{{br /}}}

        {{{br/}}}Tap the "Swap" button to confirm the swap. If you tap the "Cancel" button, the statements will remain in their original positions. {{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}When you are satisfied with all of the statement rankings, tap the "Continue" button on the bottom right.{{{br/}}}{{{br/}}}
        If you want to see these instructions again, tap the "?" button at the top of the main page.{{{br /}}}{{{br /}}}{{{center}}}{{{img src="https://github.com/shawnbanasick/quince/blob/development/src/assets/helpSymbol.png?raw=true" width="30"/}}}
